column5: Was wondering if these 2 are the exact same creek or branch differently. I see in the regulation book they have the same opener date but always thought they were 2 different creeks???
Are you speaking of the creeks along the ranger lake rd?
SAME CREEK, iTS KNOWN AS HORNER ABOVE PRINCETON. OPENER WOULD BE THE SAME FOR ALL STREAMS IN SOUTHERN ONTARIO LAST SATURDAY IN APRIL.
No I'm trying to locate Horner creek but whitemans creek pops up and was told it was in Drumbo? But can't seem to find it in maps
You mean fourth Saturday, not last.

No I'm trying to locate Horner creek but whitemans creek pops up and was told it was in Drumbo? But can't seem to find it in maps As stated Whitemans above Princeton is Horner Creek    http://i115.photobucket.com/albums/n308/kookyzone/Letter%208.5%20x%2011_zpsqonplslt.jpg

Horner flows into whitemans a little northwest of drumbo. I wouldnt get to excited about it Ontario out of doors did a write up about it some 8 years ago and its been fished to crap. It was a good spot before everybody and their brother goes there now
